WEBVTT

00:00.901 --> 00:02.402
Last season
on the practice...

00:02.435 --> 00:03.403
Aah!

00:03.436 --> 00:04.505
What?

00:04.538 --> 00:05.772
There's a head
in the bag!

00:05.806 --> 00:07.107
The woman I met last night.

00:07.140 --> 00:08.642
What are you doing
with her head?

00:08.675 --> 00:09.710
Somebody put it there.

00:09.743 --> 00:11.111
George Vogelman, you are
under arrest

00:11.144 --> 00:13.046
for the murder
of Susan Robin.

00:13.079 --> 00:15.248
We both know I've always
had some motive

00:15.281 --> 00:16.683
to tell you I'm innocent,

00:16.717 --> 00:19.285
but now, the evidence
being closed,

00:19.319 --> 00:23.524
it doesn't matter
what I tell you.

00:23.557 --> 00:26.059
I didn't do it.

00:28.494 --> 00:30.430
MAN: We find the defendant,
George Vogelman,

00:30.463 --> 00:34.300
not guilty.

00:39.205 --> 00:40.541
(gasps)

00:40.574 --> 00:42.308
Ugh!

00:42.342 --> 00:45.478
Some guy stabbed me.

00:45.512 --> 00:49.349
Guy? You said --
you said "nun."

00:49.382 --> 00:55.221
It was a guy
in a nun suit.

00:59.325 --> 01:02.362
Is it really so terrible
if they see the videotape?

01:02.395 --> 01:03.697
It ain't great.

01:03.730 --> 01:05.832
We don't want the jury
inflamed over the images.

01:05.866 --> 01:07.367
We better get going.

01:07.400 --> 01:08.702
We're all set.

01:08.735 --> 01:09.836
Where's your wife?

01:09.870 --> 01:11.705
Jimmy said
we didn't need her.

01:11.738 --> 01:12.673
It's just a hearing.

01:12.706 --> 01:15.509
I want her there for trial.
Your kids, too.

01:15.542 --> 01:18.545
We're going to be late.
Let's go.

01:22.816 --> 01:23.784
Thank you.

01:23.817 --> 01:25.185
You're welcome.

01:25.218 --> 01:26.419
Elleanor?

01:28.622 --> 01:31.658
George, hey.

01:31.692 --> 01:34.127
My co-op association
just evicted me

01:34.160 --> 01:36.129
on grounds
of moral turpitude.

01:36.162 --> 01:38.464
-Excuse me?
-They're saying even though
I was acquitted

01:38.498 --> 01:40.333
in the Susan Robin case,

01:40.366 --> 01:42.803
in their minds it isn't clear
that I'm innocent,

01:42.836 --> 01:44.805
and they voted me out.

01:44.838 --> 01:47.473
How many times
do I have to keep paying

01:47.508 --> 01:49.342
for something I didn't do?

01:49.375 --> 01:50.877
They evicted you
from the building?

01:50.911 --> 01:53.747
30 days notice.
Is this legal?

01:53.780 --> 01:55.882
I wouldn't want a killer
on my floor.

01:55.916 --> 01:57.751
-Lucy.
-Well, not that you are one.

01:57.784 --> 02:00.787
George,
I'm just saying that...

02:00.821 --> 02:03.289
Will you represent me,
Elleanor?

02:03.323 --> 02:05.826
I know it's not
a big case, but --

02:05.859 --> 02:08.127
I brought my lease
with me.

02:11.331 --> 02:13.166
Okay. Sure.

02:13.199 --> 02:15.636
In the conference room,
we'll review it.

02:15.669 --> 02:18.672
Thank you.
I feel better already.

02:19.940 --> 02:22.208
He's back.

02:23.944 --> 02:27.147
â™ª

03:12.458 --> 03:15.428
This is how
she was found, your honor.

03:15.461 --> 03:16.462
You can see the slight
bruising on her neck.

03:16.496 --> 03:19.399
This is how the police
found her?

03:19.432 --> 03:20.801
They hadn't moved her.

03:20.834 --> 03:24.304
Okay, here.
Now, this isn't blood.

03:24.337 --> 03:25.672
It's grape jelly.

03:25.706 --> 03:26.807
Grape jelly?

03:26.840 --> 03:28.308
Yes, your honor.

03:28.341 --> 03:29.843
What else?

03:29.876 --> 03:32.679
That's it. 30 seconds
of footage, tops.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.848
That footage
is so inflammatory --

03:34.881 --> 03:37.584
it goes to what
the scene looked like.

03:37.618 --> 03:39.586
Why can't the jury
be allowed --

03:39.620 --> 03:40.721
they'll look at that
and be horrified

03:40.754 --> 03:42.556
and decide someone's
got to pay.

03:42.589 --> 03:43.757
You know what?

03:43.790 --> 03:46.326
This idea that we have to
shelter juries from the truth,

03:46.359 --> 03:47.928
that was started
by defense attorneys.

03:47.961 --> 03:50.697
-Already with the speeches.
We haven't even begun.
-You think that's a speech?

03:50.731 --> 03:52.132
All right.

03:52.165 --> 03:54.735
Your honor I have no
intention of getting on a
soapbox believe me,

03:54.768 --> 03:57.838
but how did it happen
that we became afraid

03:57.871 --> 04:00.006
of letting juries
see things for themselves?

04:00.040 --> 04:02.475
This footage describes
the scene more accurately

04:02.509 --> 04:04.310
than could any
testimonial account.

04:04.344 --> 04:06.012
This system
is supposed to be

04:06.046 --> 04:07.614
about arriving
at the truth.

04:07.648 --> 04:09.616
I don't see why
the straightest-line approach

04:09.650 --> 04:11.618
should be eliminated
from the process.

04:11.652 --> 04:13.053
We cling to this notion

04:13.086 --> 04:15.522
that the jury system
is the best in the world,

04:15.556 --> 04:18.058
all the while
we don't trust them.
It is absurd it is indecent

04:18.091 --> 04:20.894
It is an insult
to this room

04:20.927 --> 04:23.530
and to the people in the name of
civic duty who sit in that box.

04:23.564 --> 04:26.900
Yes, and I'm so glad you left
your soapbox at home.

04:26.933 --> 04:28.802
The issue
before this court goes

04:28.835 --> 04:31.471
to whether or not my client
committed the crime.

04:31.505 --> 04:33.674
The district attorney,
by his own admission,

04:33.707 --> 04:35.375
agrees this footage
doesn't speak to that.

04:35.408 --> 04:36.677
We've stipulated
to strangulation --

04:36.710 --> 04:38.378
I'm not offering --

04:38.411 --> 04:39.780
can I finish?

04:39.813 --> 04:42.082
You don't need to finish we
already know what you're going
to say.

04:42.115 --> 04:44.084
You got a sick depraved,
murdering client like always,

04:44.117 --> 04:45.952
and like always,

04:45.986 --> 04:48.655
the more truth you can keep
under wraps, the better.

04:48.689 --> 04:50.657
It is a disgrace regularly
visited upon this room

04:50.691 --> 04:52.959
by you and every other
defense attorney.

04:52.993 --> 04:54.695
Napoleon complex, your honor --

04:54.728 --> 04:56.563
res ipsa pipsqueak.

04:56.597 --> 04:58.398
All right.

04:58.431 --> 05:01.434
The videotape is allowed.

05:01.467 --> 05:03.570
Whatever's between
the two of you,

05:03.604 --> 05:06.006
keep it out of the room.

05:06.039 --> 05:09.109
We'll bring the jury in
at 11:00.

05:09.142 --> 05:11.578
Do you really think
that was necessary?

05:11.612 --> 05:13.580
Yes.
Any word from Rebecca?

05:13.614 --> 05:16.550
The sister agreed
to at least talk to her.
She should be there now.

05:16.583 --> 05:17.818
Where's your family?

05:17.851 --> 05:19.720
My wife and son
are coming.

05:19.753 --> 05:21.555
My daughter's 11.
I don't want her here.

05:21.588 --> 05:23.456
Call me a pipsqueak?

05:23.489 --> 05:24.891
Get away from me, Richard,
before I trip over you.

05:24.925 --> 05:26.627
LINDSAY: All right.

05:26.660 --> 05:27.994
I'll get you, Donnell.

05:28.028 --> 05:30.697
I'll get your client,
I'll get you.

05:30.731 --> 05:33.099
Richard,
what are you doing?

05:33.133 --> 05:35.569
He called me a pipsqueak
in open court.

05:35.602 --> 05:37.571
Richard,
you're a district attorney.

05:37.604 --> 05:40.106
You can't be yelling
"I'll get you"

05:40.140 --> 05:42.743
to defense lawyers
in the corridor.

05:42.776 --> 05:44.578
How's the case?

05:44.611 --> 05:46.880
Circumstantial but tight,
although you never know

05:46.913 --> 05:49.616
what your little friends
are going to pull.

05:49.650 --> 05:51.818
Just don't be screaming
at them

05:51.852 --> 05:53.119
in the corridor,
all right?

05:53.153 --> 05:54.487
All right.

05:55.922 --> 05:58.592
Call me a pipsqueak.

05:59.526 --> 06:01.595
This man
was judged innocent.

06:01.628 --> 06:02.963
So was O. J. Simpson,

06:02.996 --> 06:05.165
but that doesn't mean
a co-op has to welcome --

06:05.198 --> 06:07.501
How many times does he have
to be victimized?

06:07.534 --> 06:10.003
First he's put on trial,
and after an acquittal,

06:10.036 --> 06:12.773
the police plant a knife
in my office trying to
get him again.

06:12.806 --> 06:15.742
The reason the police did that
because they remain convinced

06:15.776 --> 06:18.645
that he cut off
a woman's head.

06:18.679 --> 06:20.647
He's supposed
to walk around branded?

06:20.681 --> 06:22.482
I sympathize, counsel,

06:22.516 --> 06:24.651
but an acquittal
in a criminal trial

06:24.685 --> 06:26.520
does not add up
to innocence.

06:26.553 --> 06:28.054
It simply means
that the state

06:28.088 --> 06:30.190
couldn't make
its burden of proof.

06:30.223 --> 06:31.191
How about O. J. Simpson?

06:31.224 --> 06:33.794
Do you think that a co-op
should be required

06:33.827 --> 06:35.662
to keep him as a member?

06:35.696 --> 06:37.931
First of all, O. J. Simpson
was found guilty

06:37.964 --> 06:39.499
in a civil trial.

06:39.533 --> 06:42.068
As Mr. Vogelman probably
would be if a civil trial --

06:42.102 --> 06:43.670
you don't know that.

06:43.704 --> 06:46.072
Look, he could be
a very nice man who,

06:46.106 --> 06:47.908
by coincidence,
happened to have

06:47.941 --> 06:50.210
a human head pop out
of his medical bag,

06:50.243 --> 06:52.813
but people in the building
have started to move out

06:52.846 --> 06:54.681
since he moved in.

06:54.715 --> 06:55.949
They feel threatened.
And by the way

06:55.982 --> 06:57.918
co-ops have always
been allowed

06:57.951 --> 07:00.053
to pick and choose
their members.

07:00.086 --> 07:01.688
They're not allowed
to discriminate.

07:01.722 --> 07:03.690
No, if he were being heaved

07:03.724 --> 07:06.226
because of the color
of his skin,

07:06.259 --> 07:09.195
because of his religion,
he'd have a case.

07:09.229 --> 07:11.932
But we're certainly allowed
to ask on the application,

07:11.965 --> 07:14.568
"have you ever been charged
with a decapitation?"

07:14.601 --> 07:17.203
Maybe it was a mistake
to leave that question off.

07:17.237 --> 07:18.204
You think you're funny?

07:18.238 --> 07:19.840
Would you live in the
same building as him?

07:19.873 --> 07:23.944
Alright, I'll take it
under advisement.

07:23.977 --> 07:26.713
Give me till
the morning -- 10:00.

07:31.251 --> 07:33.219
How dare you ask me that?

07:33.253 --> 07:35.556
I understand
this is difficult.

07:35.589 --> 07:36.823
My sister is murdered,

07:36.857 --> 07:39.993
and, what, you plan
to put her on trial?

07:40.026 --> 07:42.729
Ms. Poole, The prosecution
thinks there was
something going on

07:42.763 --> 07:44.731
between your sister
and Dr. Olson.

07:44.765 --> 07:47.868
There wasn't. She liked
clean teeth, he's a dentist.

07:47.901 --> 07:49.870
Ok, then Is it possible
she could have been

07:49.903 --> 07:51.872
having an affair
with somebody else?

07:51.905 --> 07:52.873
No.

07:52.906 --> 07:54.107
What about her ex-husband?

07:54.140 --> 07:56.009
Your client killed her,
Ms. Washington.

07:56.042 --> 07:57.878
He was obsessed with her,

07:57.911 --> 08:00.614
and he killed her because
she wasn't interested in him,

08:00.647 --> 08:04.718
and I can't believe you
actually expect me to help you.

08:04.751 --> 08:06.753
Did your sister
like bugs?

08:09.189 --> 08:10.724
Excuse me?

08:10.757 --> 08:12.726
There was a container
filled with bugs, cockroaches.

08:12.759 --> 08:14.728
It was found
at the scene.

08:14.761 --> 08:17.263
The police don't know
how it got there.

08:17.297 --> 08:19.766
Did she like bugs?

08:22.168 --> 08:24.304
And no other fingerprints
belonged to anybody

08:24.337 --> 08:26.306
other than the victim
or the defendant.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.041
What else did you find,
detective?

08:28.074 --> 08:30.644
We retrieved a pair
of latex gloves

08:30.677 --> 08:32.145
from a trash container.

08:32.178 --> 08:35.616
DNA analysis revealed they
were worn by the defendant.

08:35.649 --> 08:37.784
The DNA samples were...

08:37.818 --> 08:41.254
Oils from skin flakes
on the inside of the gloves.

08:41.287 --> 08:44.290
And on the outside
of the gloves?

08:44.324 --> 08:47.060
Skin secretions
from the victim

08:47.093 --> 08:49.162
and traces of grape jelly.

08:49.195 --> 08:51.064
Grape jelly?

08:51.097 --> 08:53.934
Yes. Her mouth was filled
with grape jelly.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.637
Anything else, detective?

08:56.670 --> 08:59.640
We found several pictures
of the victim

08:59.673 --> 09:00.941
in the defendant's desk.

09:06.847 --> 09:09.315
Who called you
and reported this crime?

09:09.349 --> 09:10.316
Dr. Olson.

09:10.350 --> 09:11.652
When you got there,

09:11.685 --> 09:14.688
did he tell you he tried
to clear her airways
when he walked in,

09:14.721 --> 09:16.690
discovering
her mouth all clogged?

09:16.723 --> 09:18.692
He said that, yes.

09:18.725 --> 09:20.060
If somebody reached in

09:20.093 --> 09:22.062
to clear
Ms. Poole's mouth out,

09:22.095 --> 09:25.165
he'd get jelly on his hands
or gloves, don't you think?

09:25.198 --> 09:26.700
Objection -- speculation.

09:26.733 --> 09:28.835
We're only here
because of speculation.

09:28.869 --> 09:31.104
Sustained. Let's move on.

09:31.137 --> 09:33.707
Detective, are you aware
that Ms. Poole

09:33.740 --> 09:36.810
sought and obtained
a restraining order

09:36.843 --> 09:37.844
against her ex-husband
two years ago?

09:37.878 --> 09:40.246
Yes. We questioned
Mr. Jenson

09:40.280 --> 09:42.816
and ruled him out
as a suspect,

09:42.849 --> 09:44.685
if that's where
you're going.

09:44.718 --> 09:46.687
You can't rule out
the possibility

09:46.720 --> 09:48.855
of somebody else coming
into that room, can you?

09:48.889 --> 09:51.257
No evidence points to anyone
other than Dr. Olson.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.259
But you can't exclude
the possibility

09:53.293 --> 09:54.327
of somebody else
coming into that room.

09:54.360 --> 09:57.731
DETECTIVE: No I can't,
but fibers from his gloves

09:57.764 --> 09:59.165
were found on her neck
and nobody else's.

09:59.199 --> 10:03.136
Yes and if my client were
performing mouth-to-mouth
resuscitation,

10:03.169 --> 10:05.405
would it be possible
for fibers of the gloves

10:05.438 --> 10:07.107
to get on
the victim's neck?

10:07.140 --> 10:09.275
I have no idea.

10:09.309 --> 10:11.044
You have no idea.

10:12.879 --> 10:15.415
Well, let's leave it at that.

10:15.448 --> 10:18.018
The detective has no idea.

10:25.892 --> 10:27.861
Do you have a second?

10:27.894 --> 10:31.031
Would this be ex parte?

10:31.064 --> 10:34.735
It may or may not be.
I'll let you be the judge.

10:34.768 --> 10:36.169
Gee, thanks.

10:36.202 --> 10:40.406
When I saw that this case
was going to your division,

10:40.440 --> 10:42.876
I thought about bringing
a motion to recuse you

10:42.909 --> 10:45.879
since both you
and George Vogelman

10:45.912 --> 10:47.881
had inadvertently been
listed as suspects

10:47.914 --> 10:49.883
after Lindsay Dole
was stabbed.

10:49.916 --> 10:53.319
I know it's not
a direct conflict, but...

10:53.353 --> 10:56.790
Well, after seeing the anger
of George Vogelman

10:56.823 --> 10:59.926
and what a false accusation
can do to a person,

10:59.960 --> 11:02.796
I have to be honest
and ask the question --

11:02.829 --> 11:05.331
can you see straight
on this issue?

11:05.365 --> 11:08.034
Can I see straight
on the issue

11:08.068 --> 11:11.938
of being falsely accused
of something?

11:11.972 --> 11:12.806
Yes.

11:12.839 --> 11:14.808
Well, if I couldn't,

11:14.841 --> 11:19.079
wouldn't my bias
run in your favor?

11:19.112 --> 11:20.814
I don't know.

11:20.847 --> 11:23.183
You don't know?

11:23.216 --> 11:25.786
Any thoughts
as to how this case

11:25.819 --> 11:28.922
ended up before me,
counsel?

11:28.955 --> 11:32.926
It's because you went
to the favor bank

11:32.959 --> 11:35.796
and you asked a certain
clerk named Benny

11:35.829 --> 11:39.365
to make sure this case
dropped into my lap,

11:39.399 --> 11:42.969
figuring my bias
would work for you.

11:43.003 --> 11:48.241
I see a lot straighter
than I'm given credit for.

11:48.274 --> 11:49.843
As I said,

11:49.876 --> 11:52.345
I will take the matter
under advisement.

11:52.378 --> 11:53.847
In the meantime,

11:53.880 --> 11:56.382
get your ass out
of my chambers.

12:10.130 --> 12:11.898
She would come in
twice a week

12:11.932 --> 12:13.433
to have
her teeth cleaned.

12:13.466 --> 12:14.835
Every week?

12:14.868 --> 12:16.102
Yes.

12:16.136 --> 12:18.905
She had this compulsive
thing about her teeth.

12:18.939 --> 12:21.241
She'd brush them
12 times a day

12:21.274 --> 12:23.777
and come in twice a week
for plaque removal.

12:23.810 --> 12:26.246
Were you ever there
for any of these cleanings?

12:26.279 --> 12:29.182
No. He did them himself,
which was odd.

12:29.215 --> 12:31.317
I'm the hygienist.

12:31.351 --> 12:33.386
He wanted to do them.

12:33.419 --> 12:35.388
Yes, then he started
scheduling her

12:35.421 --> 12:37.057
for early mornings,

12:37.090 --> 12:39.059
before the office
was even open.

12:39.092 --> 12:42.563
Did you ever witness any
of these early encounters?

12:42.596 --> 12:44.865
One time I came in early.

12:44.898 --> 12:46.867
The door
to the examination room

12:46.900 --> 12:48.334
slammed shut in a hurry.

12:48.368 --> 12:52.405
Dr. Olson then told me
I was never to come in early

12:52.438 --> 12:53.940
like that again.

12:53.974 --> 12:55.876
Did you find this strange?

12:55.909 --> 12:56.843
Of course,

12:56.877 --> 12:59.546
but I found the whole thing
very strange.

12:59.580 --> 13:02.015
Anything else
you find strange?

13:02.048 --> 13:03.950
Well...

13:03.984 --> 13:06.286
I'm also in charge
of accounts receivable.

13:06.319 --> 13:08.955
He instructed me
not to bill her.

13:08.989 --> 13:11.424
Two visits a week
for over a year --

13:11.457 --> 13:14.294
that's a lot of time
not billed.

13:14.327 --> 13:17.097
BOBBY: So if I'm clear,
the crux of your testimony

13:17.130 --> 13:19.432
is that he cleaned
her teeth twice a week

13:19.465 --> 13:21.902
early in the morning
and didn't bill her,

13:21.935 --> 13:23.369
and you found that strange.

13:23.403 --> 13:24.505
Basically.

13:24.538 --> 13:25.906
Thank you.

13:25.939 --> 13:27.908
Do you have any reason
to believe

13:27.941 --> 13:30.043
that she wasn't really
getting her teeth cleaned
on these visits?

13:30.076 --> 13:32.913
No, I believe she was
getting them cleaned.

13:32.946 --> 13:35.315
She had this thing
about it.

13:35.348 --> 13:38.351
Thank you, Ms. Heinz.
That's all.

13:40.220 --> 13:41.588
You got no case.

13:41.622 --> 13:43.924
Gee, I guess I should
just give up then.

13:43.957 --> 13:45.391
You got fingerprints
and a suspicious hygienist.

13:45.425 --> 13:47.393
I got two people
in a room,

13:47.427 --> 13:48.929
one ends up strangled.

13:48.962 --> 13:50.063
What's that, suicide?

13:50.096 --> 13:51.998
You've got no case.

13:52.032 --> 13:53.333
Mr. Donnell?

13:53.366 --> 13:55.001
I'm Bob Jenson.

13:55.035 --> 13:57.070
I used to be married
to the woman who was killed,

13:57.103 --> 13:58.872
and I don't appreciate
your innuendo

13:58.905 --> 14:00.406
that I might be a suspect.

14:00.440 --> 14:01.942
Mr. Jenson, I sympathize

14:01.975 --> 14:03.644
