28:08.254 --> 28:09.756
Jimmy.

28:09.790 --> 28:11.925
We're up against it,
Henry.

28:11.958 --> 28:14.227
I'm not saying
I think you did it --

28:14.260 --> 28:16.196
I'll say it.

28:16.229 --> 28:19.199
I don't believe you
anymore, Henry.

28:19.232 --> 28:21.034
Allison...

28:21.067 --> 28:25.171
Listening to you up there.

28:25.205 --> 28:26.907
You're sick.

28:26.940 --> 28:29.776
-You're just
a very sick person.
-Honey.

28:29.810 --> 28:32.813
Our children are going
to have to read about this.

28:34.981 --> 28:36.950
Could you give us
a moment?

28:36.983 --> 28:39.720
Sure.

28:54.535 --> 28:56.503
I don't know where to go --

28:56.537 --> 29:00.106
hatch a theory
he was being framed or...
I don't know.

29:00.140 --> 29:01.842
We should have
been digging

29:01.875 --> 29:03.910
into who else wanted
that woman dead.

29:03.944 --> 29:05.445
-We did dig into that.
-JIMMY: Not enough we didn't.

29:05.478 --> 29:07.047
She's into stuff
that kinky,

29:07.080 --> 29:10.851
who knows what people
she was mixed up with?

29:10.884 --> 29:12.919
He gets an annuity.
You know about that?

29:12.953 --> 29:14.054
Olson?

29:14.087 --> 29:15.321
From his father,

29:15.355 --> 29:18.258
-an annual annuity
of $125,000.
-So?

29:18.291 --> 29:20.126
So?

29:20.160 --> 29:22.228
Anybody thought
about plan "B"?

29:22.262 --> 29:24.865
Plan "B"? Who?
The ex has an alibi.

29:24.898 --> 29:26.232
Henry's wife.

29:26.266 --> 29:27.267
What?

29:27.300 --> 29:30.270
She got an alibi?
Think about it.

29:30.303 --> 29:32.105
Maybe she found out about
her husband's secret.

29:32.138 --> 29:33.774
Maybe she wanted revenge.

29:33.807 --> 29:37.143
Problem is if she kills him,
there goes the annuity and
she loses a lot of money.

29:37.177 --> 29:39.279
Better to frame him,
get him stuck in jail.

29:39.312 --> 29:41.214
Come on.

29:41.247 --> 29:44.284
Look, she probably has keys to
his offices. Maybe know's
his routines? Sneaks in
kills the girl.

29:44.317 --> 29:46.052
First of all, the police
checked her out.

29:46.086 --> 29:47.854
And accepted her word
that she was home.

29:47.888 --> 29:48.989
Well I know Allison --

29:49.022 --> 29:50.991
you said you knew Henry,

29:51.024 --> 29:53.393
-and you didn't know he was
cheating with a cockroach.
-Funny.

29:53.426 --> 29:55.261
If she doesn't really
have an alibi,

29:55.295 --> 29:57.130
maybe we could
plan "B" her.

29:57.163 --> 29:59.600
Bobby, there's no way
this woman killed her.

29:59.633 --> 30:02.135
Whether it's true or not
doesn't matter.

30:02.168 --> 30:03.203
The point is
you could sell it.

30:03.236 --> 30:06.206
I mean, at least enough
to make reasonable doubt.

30:06.239 --> 30:08.441
I thought you were out
of that business, Eugene --

30:08.474 --> 30:10.310
falsely accusing people
of murder.

30:10.343 --> 30:12.478
Last time we did this,
we got sued.

30:12.513 --> 30:14.014
I'm just throwing it
out there.

30:14.047 --> 30:17.150
You said you got an innocent
man for murder.I didn't
think you'd be too fussy

30:17.183 --> 30:18.418
over how you
got him acquitted.

30:18.451 --> 30:19.485
What was her statement?

30:19.520 --> 30:21.487
Home alone,
kids were at school.

30:21.522 --> 30:23.156
The police did confirm

30:23.189 --> 30:25.425
that the car
never left the Driveway.

30:25.458 --> 30:26.960
People take buses.

30:26.993 --> 30:28.161
It's too desperate.

30:28.194 --> 30:30.163
We are desperate, Jimmy.

30:30.196 --> 30:32.432
Your buddy was last seen
with the victim, he lies
under oath

30:32.465 --> 30:35.902
we find out that he gets
off on crushed cockroaches
he's a sick wacko.

30:35.936 --> 30:38.572
You don't know what
you're talking about.

30:38.605 --> 30:40.440
Let's just concentrate --

30:40.473 --> 30:42.375
Hold on. Hold on.

30:42.408 --> 30:43.910
Assuming this is an option,

30:43.944 --> 30:46.580
we call her and ask
to treat her hostile?

30:46.613 --> 30:48.248
Is there another way?

30:48.281 --> 30:50.083
We've got to run it
by the client.

30:50.116 --> 30:52.619
-And he'd say no.
-Which is maybe why we don't
tell him.

30:52.653 --> 30:56.957
-He'll tip her off...
-You can't not tell the client.
Bobby what are you crazy.

30:56.990 --> 31:00.160
Hey! Do we have an obligation to
tell the client our strategy?

31:00.193 --> 31:01.962
No, we have an obligation

31:01.995 --> 31:03.897
to act in his
best interest --

31:03.930 --> 31:06.099
You can't withhold
information from the client.
That's malpractice.

31:06.132 --> 31:08.101
It's not withholding
information.

31:08.134 --> 31:10.170
You plan to accuse
his wife of murder.

31:10.203 --> 31:11.572
That's not withholding
information?

31:11.605 --> 31:13.974
We've already been sued
for this.

31:14.007 --> 31:16.309
We don't need this kind
of publicity.

31:16.342 --> 31:17.644
All right, look,

31:17.678 --> 31:21.882
let's run it by Henry,
let it be his call.

31:26.219 --> 31:28.922
You never told me
you could cook.

31:28.955 --> 31:30.190
This is delicious.

31:30.223 --> 31:33.326
Two secrets --
first, butter.

31:33.359 --> 31:34.327
Butter?

31:34.360 --> 31:37.130
I smear the whole bird.
It seeps in when I bake.

31:37.163 --> 31:39.933
Second,
don't carve all at once.

31:39.966 --> 31:41.935
It just Dries out the meat.

31:41.968 --> 31:45.338
I carve as I serve.

31:45.371 --> 31:46.607
You want another piece?

31:46.640 --> 31:50.476
I will have one more,
and then I am done.

31:50.511 --> 31:53.413
That is an awfully big knife
you have there, George.

31:53.446 --> 31:57.350
All the better to cut
your head off with, my dear.

31:57.383 --> 31:58.484
Bad joke.

31:58.519 --> 32:00.486
That's one for each of us.

32:00.521 --> 32:03.156
Gallows humor
is all I have left.

32:03.189 --> 32:05.959
You know, this thing
is going to follow you.

32:05.992 --> 32:07.961
People are going
to make judgments.

32:07.994 --> 32:11.231
Sometimes you can fight it,
sometimes you can't.

32:11.264 --> 32:14.367
Maybe I should just sever
the past completely

32:14.400 --> 32:16.036
and leave town.

32:16.069 --> 32:18.038
That's not the worst idea,

32:18.071 --> 32:20.941
but I'd miss you.

32:27.347 --> 32:30.350
I'll miss you, too,
Elleanor.

32:35.355 --> 32:38.324
What's the matter?

32:38.358 --> 32:40.260
I've been missing you.

32:40.293 --> 32:42.996
One good thing
about my legal woes

32:43.029 --> 32:45.265
is I've been able
to spend time with you.

32:45.298 --> 32:48.268
Remember when we used to talk
on the phone and laugh

32:48.301 --> 32:51.337
back in the days,
before you laid eyes on me?

32:51.371 --> 32:54.407
George...

32:54.440 --> 32:58.344
You're the greatest woman
I've ever known, Elleanor.
I admit it.

33:02.148 --> 33:03.684
Thank you.

33:05.185 --> 33:08.454
This is where you're
suppose to say something
nice about me.

33:09.790 --> 33:13.760
Okay, how about...

33:13.794 --> 33:17.430
I really like having you
as a friend, George.

33:17.463 --> 33:20.567
Translation --

33:20.601 --> 33:23.570
let's just stay friends.

33:46.392 --> 33:47.628
-No.
-Henry.

33:47.661 --> 33:50.430
I'm not going to let you
point the finger at her.

33:50.463 --> 33:51.565
We could lose here.
You get that?

33:51.598 --> 33:55.168
You think I win because
I accuse my own wife of murder?

33:55.201 --> 33:56.402
We'd be doing it.

33:56.436 --> 33:58.438
With my blessing.

33:58.471 --> 34:01.441
You want to risk prison
the rest of your life?
Is that what I'm hearing?

34:01.474 --> 34:04.678
Allison could not possibly
have done this.
You know her.

34:04.711 --> 34:05.746
It doesn't matter.

34:05.779 --> 34:09.449
She's a red herring
to give us reasonable doubt.

34:09.482 --> 34:10.717
This is crazy, Jimmy.

34:10.751 --> 34:13.253
What jury is going
to believe --

34:13.286 --> 34:15.789
it isn't crazy.
Think about it.

34:15.822 --> 34:18.190
Don't get me wrong.

34:18.224 --> 34:20.527
I'm not saying
I think she did it,

34:20.561 --> 34:22.529
but the idea she did --

34:22.563 --> 34:25.532
you said yourself you two
had a big screaming fight

34:25.565 --> 34:28.268
over this bug fetish thing.

34:28.301 --> 34:30.804
Maybe she figured
it was going on at work.

34:30.837 --> 34:33.806
If the door was locked,
she'd have a key, right?

34:33.840 --> 34:36.543
You kept your appointments
in your computer at home.

34:36.577 --> 34:38.812
She'd know if anybody
would be there.

34:38.844 --> 34:41.481
She knew your office hours
of business.

34:41.514 --> 34:44.150
Can you be positive
she didn't go down there?

34:44.184 --> 34:46.652
Yes, I can.

34:55.195 --> 35:00.915
Me and you...
Lawyer privilege?
Friend privilege?

35:03.504 --> 35:05.238
Me and you?

35:06.707 --> 35:08.642
Sure.

35:09.275 --> 35:14.781
You were close.
It was Steven.

35:16.216 --> 35:19.520
What?

35:19.553 --> 35:21.454
Your son Steven?

35:21.487 --> 35:24.525
I saw the door close
on him when he left.

35:24.558 --> 35:27.393
I think he must have
come down,

35:27.427 --> 35:28.529
maybe discovered --

35:28.562 --> 35:29.796
Why haven't you told
anybody this?

35:29.830 --> 35:32.799
Because I don't want him
to spend the rest of
his life in jail

35:32.833 --> 35:35.536
for something
I drove him to.

35:35.569 --> 35:37.904
Now look you said I had
a very good chance

35:37.938 --> 35:39.506
of beating this thing.

35:39.540 --> 35:41.508
That's what
I've decided to do.

35:41.542 --> 35:43.276
He's letting you
take the fall?

35:43.309 --> 35:45.546
Oh, he's so angry with me,
he doesn't care.

35:45.579 --> 35:47.681
He doesn't even know
I know.

35:51.718 --> 35:53.820
Let me go to the D. A.

35:53.854 --> 35:55.956
Absolutely not!
No chance!

35:55.989 --> 35:58.525
They will try him
as an adult.

35:58.559 --> 36:00.827
You know that, Jimmy.
His life will be over.

36:00.861 --> 36:01.795
What if he kills --

36:01.828 --> 36:03.697
-Well I'll get him help.
-No Henry you can't.

36:03.730 --> 36:06.833
This is between you and me.
You gave me your word.

36:06.867 --> 36:10.403
You say anything to anybody,

36:10.436 --> 36:12.438
I'll confess to the crime.

36:15.308 --> 36:19.412
This happened because of me,

36:19.445 --> 36:22.749
and I'm willing
to take the risk.

36:34.628 --> 36:38.632
Okay. Closing arguments.

36:42.636 --> 36:44.871
Does it look bad?

36:44.905 --> 36:46.607
Of course it does.

36:46.640 --> 36:48.875
She was strangled
in his dental chair --

36:48.909 --> 36:52.746
no prints belonging
to anybody else.

36:52.779 --> 36:54.748
We know
he's a little twisted --

36:54.781 --> 36:58.585
sexually aroused
by seeing bugs get crushed?

36:58.619 --> 36:59.986
What's with that?

37:00.020 --> 37:03.624
It looks really bad,

37:03.657 --> 37:07.493
but he didn't do it.

37:07.528 --> 37:10.631
Who did?

37:10.664 --> 37:12.332
I don't know.

37:12.365 --> 37:14.635
I do know the victim
put herself out there

37:14.668 --> 37:17.604
on the internet
advertising her services,

37:17.638 --> 37:19.906
and you encounter a lot
of depraved people

37:19.940 --> 37:21.908
doing that kind of thing.

37:21.942 --> 37:24.477
Maybe she was stalked
that day.

37:24.511 --> 37:26.747
Maybe she was followed
to my client's office.

37:26.780 --> 37:29.482
Maybe her routine
was known to the killer

37:29.516 --> 37:32.919
and this presented
the perfect opportunity.

37:32.953 --> 37:34.655
I don't know.

37:34.688 --> 37:36.022
Neither do they.

37:36.056 --> 37:39.660
All they can prove
with the physical evidence

37:39.693 --> 37:43.764
is that my client was
in the same room as the victim.

37:43.797 --> 37:45.532
Well, he admitted that.

37:45.566 --> 37:47.768
In fact, he called the police,
didn't he?

37:47.801 --> 37:48.935
And think about this.

37:48.969 --> 37:50.937
If he was going
to kill somebody,

37:50.971 --> 37:52.673
would he do it this way --

37:52.706 --> 37:55.676
strangle the person
in his own office,

37:55.709 --> 37:57.811
put grape jelly
in her mouth,

37:57.844 --> 38:00.814
leave his gloves
in the room?

38:00.847 --> 38:03.550
Wouldn't he try
to get away with it?

38:03.584 --> 38:07.053
Why didn't he?
Because he didn't do it.

38:07.087 --> 38:09.690
And they have no physical
or testimonial evidence

38:09.723 --> 38:13.293
to prove that he did.

38:17.698 --> 38:21.802
He kept her pictures,
cleaned her teeth for free

38:21.835 --> 38:24.705
while she squished
cockroaches.

38:24.738 --> 38:27.708
Maybe she said she wasn't
going to do it anymore

38:27.741 --> 38:29.843
and he snapped.

38:29.876 --> 38:33.847
We could stand here all day
trying to make sense of it,

38:33.880 --> 38:37.083
but you can't make sense
of depravities,

38:37.117 --> 38:38.719
ladies and gentlemen,

38:38.752 --> 38:42.589
whether it be a murder
or a bug fetish.

38:42.623 --> 38:46.560
It's pointless
to apply reason.

38:46.593 --> 38:48.829
No evidence points
to anybody else

38:48.862 --> 38:51.865
being in that room
other than the defendant.

38:51.898 --> 38:54.134
The woman he engages
to come to his office

38:54.167 --> 38:58.572
to squish insects
and bring him to a climax

38:58.605 --> 39:00.440
is found dead.

39:00.473 --> 39:05.612
Him and her,
she ends up strangled.

39:05.646 --> 39:07.614
We caught him in a lie

39:07.648 --> 39:10.116
right here
on the witness stand.

39:10.150 --> 39:13.754
We already know he's a liar.

39:13.787 --> 39:16.456
Is there really
even a question here

39:16.489 --> 39:20.360
that he's also a murderer?

39:24.765 --> 39:26.099
Elleanor.

39:26.132 --> 39:27.734
Hey, George.

39:27.768 --> 39:28.735
Come on in.

39:28.769 --> 39:30.837
Actually, I'm running late
for a deposition.

39:30.871 --> 39:32.839
I just stopped by to...

39:32.873 --> 39:36.643
Well, I'm just feeling
a little uncomfortable

39:36.677 --> 39:38.645
about last night's kiss.

39:38.679 --> 39:40.113
Oh?

39:40.146 --> 39:42.916
I've been thinking
about it all night,

39:42.949 --> 39:44.450
and you know, George,

39:44.484 --> 39:46.853
your trial was the biggest
professional victory

39:46.887 --> 39:48.188
of my life.

39:48.221 --> 39:50.657
It was pretty big
for me, too.

39:50.691 --> 39:52.659
But I mean I think,
on some level,

39:52.693 --> 39:55.662
I try to relive that victory
every chance I get,

39:55.696 --> 39:59.065
and being in your company,
on some unconscious --

39:59.099 --> 40:02.736
I just think I feel
better about myself

40:02.769 --> 40:04.605
when I'm with you.

40:04.638 --> 40:06.673
You kissed me on some
professional high?

40:06.707 --> 40:11.077
No, no, it's not that.

40:11.111 --> 40:16.082
I like being with you
because...

40:16.116 --> 40:18.084
What I came here to say

40:18.118 --> 40:21.955
is that our friendship
is very complicated,

40:21.988 --> 40:24.691
and my kissing you

40:24.725 --> 40:27.828
is probably not going
to happen again,

40:27.861 --> 40:30.764
and I just want
to be clear on that,

40:30.797 --> 40:33.166
that we just keep it
as friends.

40:33.199 --> 40:36.036
Okay.

40:36.069 --> 40:37.704
I understand.

40:37.738 --> 40:39.239
Do you?

40:39.272 --> 40:41.575
I get it, Elleanor.

40:41.608 --> 40:44.044
You okay with that?

40:44.077 --> 40:47.113
Yes.

40:47.147 --> 40:50.116
I appreciate your
coming here to tell me.

40:50.150 --> 40:54.054
Well, good.

40:54.087 --> 40:55.922
See you soon?

40:55.956 --> 40:58.191
Absolutely.

40:58.224 --> 41:02.863
Well, I got
that deposition, so...

41:02.896 --> 41:05.532
All right.

41:05.566 --> 41:06.867
Bye.

41:06.900 --> 41:08.902
Bye.

41:20.313 --> 41:21.948
You're worried
about your son.

41:21.982 --> 41:23.950
How's he going
to be better off --

41:23.984 --> 41:25.719
He'll be better off
out of prison.

41:25.752 --> 41:28.121
Listen to me Henry, once that
verdict comes back,

41:28.154 --> 41:29.856
we have no credibility.

41:29.890 --> 41:32.225
You're just a guilty man
trying some desperate act --

41:32.258 --> 41:34.961
unless it comes back
not guilty.

41:34.995 --> 41:36.697
You yourself said
we have a decent chance.

41:36.730 --> 41:37.698
But it's a risk.

41:37.731 --> 41:39.232
A risk I'm willing to take.

41:39.265 --> 41:40.100
Henry --

41:40.133 --> 41:43.003
I've made my decision.

41:45.271 --> 41:47.273
Jury's back.

42:12.899 --> 42:16.770
Will the defendant
please rise?

42:16.803 --> 42:19.105
Has the jury
reached its verdict?

42:19.139 --> 42:20.240
We have.

42:20.273 --> 42:21.975
What say you?

42:22.008 --> 42:23.309
In the matter

42:23.343 --> 42:25.311
of the commonwealth
vs Henry Olson

42:25.345 --> 42:27.648
on the charge of murder
in the first degree,

42:27.681 --> 42:30.183
we find the defendant,
Henry Olson,

42:30.216 --> 42:31.618
guilty.

42:36.356 --> 42:38.859
Your honor, the defense
notes its appeal

42:38.892 --> 42:40.326
for the record.

42:40.360 --> 42:41.995
So noted.

42:42.028 --> 42:44.330
The court officer will take
the defendant into custody.

42:44.364 --> 42:47.067
Members of the jury,
this concludes your services.
We thank you.

42:47.100 --> 42:48.802
This matter is adjourned.

42:48.835 --> 42:50.103
We have appealable issues.

42:50.136 --> 42:51.972
Can we win?

42:52.005 --> 42:53.239
I don't know.

42:53.273 --> 42:55.976
I didn't do it.
I didn't do it.

42:56.009 --> 42:57.844
ALISON: Henry!

42:57.878 --> 43:00.947
Res ipsa prison.

43:00.981 --> 43:03.684
Get out of here.

43:03.717 --> 43:05.986
What are we going to do?

43:06.019 --> 43:08.088
(sobbing)

43:08.121 --> 43:10.123
What are we going to do?

